# Building a website with Github and Jekyll
### 2015-08-20 | #docker #jekyll #github

## Intro

After a long time of => http://www.ecliptik.com www.ecliptik.com being offline I finally brought it back online with => https://pages.github.com/ Github Pages. I really like the concept of having a static site using Markdown files and a template to quickly bring online a modern looking blog without the hassle of configuring a content management system, web server, or database.

While building the site, I created a => https://github.com/ecliptik/ecliptik.github.io/blob/master/Dockerfile Dockerfile to make viewing the site locally before pushing to Github. The container image => https://hub.docker.com/r/ecliptik/jekyll/ ecliptik/jekyll built from this Dockerfile is also on Docker Hub.

